info.title: Umbraco Backoffice API
info.description: This shows all APIs available in this version of Umbraco - Including all the legacy apis that is available for backward compatibility

get.summary: Gets a page list of tracked references for the current item, so you can see where an item is being used.
get.description:
Used by info tabs on content, media etc. and for the delete and unpublish of single items.
This is basically finding parents of relations.

get.summary: Gets a page list of the child nodes of the current item used in any kind of relation.
get.description:
Used when deleting and unpublishing a single item to check if this item has any descending items that are in any
kind of relation.
This is basically finding the descending items which are children in relations.

get.summary: Gets a page list of the items used in any kind of relation from selected integer ids.
get.description:
Used when bulk deleting content/media and bulk unpublishing content (delete and unpublish on List view).
This is basically finding children of relations.

get.summary: Check if the index has been rebuilt
get.description:
This is kind of rudimentary since there's no way we can know that the index has rebuilt, we
have a listener for the index op complete so we'll just check if that key is no longer there in the runtime cache
